eir statecraft impedes more durable forms of security and inadvertently embrittles peace. At times, the United States has been the region’s bulwark against instability, but America has been a threat to Asian peace as much as it has been its guarantor. By grappling with how America fits into the Asian story, Van Jackson shows how regional stability has diminished because of U.S. choices, and why America’s margin for geopolitical error is less now than ever before.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aPeace-buildingzEast Asia. 0aPeace-buildingzSoutheast Asia. 70(DE-588)4003846-40(DE-627)10438896X0(DE-576)208852972aAußenpolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4072885-70(DE-627)1060939320(DE-576)209188553aInternationale Politik2gnd 70(DE-588)4076605-60(DE-627)1060825230(DE-576)20920236XaRegionalentwicklung2gnd 70(DE-588)4114036-90(DE-627)1042885310(DE-576)209481382aInterdependenz2gnd 70(DE-588)4116489-10(DE-627)1043252240(DE-576)209502010aSicherheitspolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4125488-00(DE-627)1057398550(DE-576)209576979aInternationales politisches System2gnd 70(DE-588)4175043-30(DE-627)10536746X0(DE-576)209960949aPolitischer Prozess2gnd 70(DE-588)7604836-60(DE-627)5602287400(DE-576)278419313aFriedenskonsolidierung2gnd 70(DE-588)7790594-50(DE-627)7003502090(DE-576)357729552aKriegsfolge2gnd 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Diplomacy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074978640uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300268713?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300268713423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300268713/original  a978-3-11-074978-6  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles